<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PrimarySourceReference/707> rdfs:label "Primary Source Reference: #707" ;
	a dprr:PrimarySourceReference ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Planc. 99" ;
	dprr:forAssertion <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertion/698> .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/505> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #505" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In place of C. Iulius who died in office (Fast. Cap. (M. Cornelius P. f. M. [- - -]); Liv. 5.31.6; 9.34.20; Dion. Hal. 1.74.5; Plut. Cam. 14.1; Degrassi 30f., 100, 386f.). The capture of Rome during this lustrum led to the rule that if one Censor died in office the other must abdicate (Liv. 5.31.6; Mommsen Str. 1.216; 2.341). They named Lucretius (above) Princeps Senatus (Plut. Cam. 32; cf. Liv. 5.55)." .
